The film series Star Trek's cinematic arm of the Star Trek franchise. Paramount Pictures began work on a film of Star Trek in 1975 after several requests from series creator Gene Roddenberry. The studio scrapped the project two years later in favor of a new television series, Star Trek: Phase II, with the original cast. However, after the huge success of Star Wars and Close Encounters of the Third Kind, Paramount changed his mind again, canceling the production of the series and adapting its pilot episode in the 1979 film Star Trek: The Motion Picture. Another five films starring the original cast followed. The cast of the spin-off series Star Trek: The Next Generation starred in four other films. A reboot and prequel to the original television series, titled simply Star Trek, was released in 2009.
